@startuml
!theme plain
title PromptFlow React Streaming Chatbot - Sequence Diagram

actor User
participant "Chatbot\n(React)" as Frontend
participant "ChatController\n(ASP.NET Core)" as Backend
participant "PromptFlow\nService" as External

User -> Frontend: Load chatbot component
activate Frontend

Frontend -> Frontend: useEffect() triggered
Frontend -> Frontend: Initialize AbortController

Frontend -> Backend: POST /api/Chat\n{chat_input, chat_history}
activate Backend

Backend -> Backend: Extract API key and URI
Backend -> Backend: Prepare request body
Backend -> Backend: Set authorization headers

Backend -> External: POST /score\nBearer token + request
activate External

External -> Backend: Stream response\n(Server-Sent Events)
Backend -> Backend: GetStreamChunks()\nProcess each chunk

loop For each streaming chunk
    External -> Backend: data: {chunk}
    Backend -> Backend: Parse JSON\nExtract chat_output
    Backend -> Frontend: SSE: data: {parsed_content}\n\n
    Frontend -> Frontend: Decode chunk
    Frontend -> Frontend: Extract data after "data: "
    Frontend -> Frontend: Append to fullText
    Frontend -> Frontend: setChatOutput(fullText)
    Frontend -> User: Update UI with new content
end

External -> Backend: Stream complete
deactivate External

Backend -> Frontend: Stream end
deactivate Backend

Frontend -> Frontend: Clean up resources
deactivate Frontend

note over Frontend, Backend
  The backend acts as a streaming proxy,
  forwarding requests to PromptFlow and
  streaming responses back to React frontend
end note

note over User, Frontend
  User sees real-time updates as
  the AI response is being streamed
end note

@enduml